How Leet code can mess with you sometimes....

1. Two Sum

Brute force [Yet less runtime in leetcode]

class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {
        int n=nums.length;
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=i;j<n;j++){
                int x=j-i;
                if(nums[x]+nums[j]==target) return new int[] {x,j};
            }            
        }
        return new int[0];        
    }
}


Optimal using Hash Maps:-

import java.util.HashMap;
class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            int diff = target - nums[i];
            if (map.containsKey(diff)) return new int[] { map.get(diff), i };
            map.put(nums[i], i);
        }
        return new int[] { -1, -1 };
    }
}
